### 🔄 Automatic Light/Dark Mode  

**For web or digital PDFs**

```css
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  .background-box {
    background-color: #232629;
    border-left: 4px solid #60B0B3;
    color: #F3F6F7;
  }
}
```

💡 When someone’s phone or computer is already using Dark Mode, the system will display the darker palette automatically; when they switch back to Light Mode, the standard soft‑blue version reappears.

**For Word / Google Docs / Canva**
- Duplicate the “Why Accessibility Choices Matter” box.  
- Label one block **Light Mode** (blue‑gray fill) and one **Dark Mode** (near‑black fill).  
- Keep them on separate layers or pages; users print or export the version that matches their preferred theme.

**Accessibility tip:**  
Always check that whichever version is active still meets the 4.5 : 1 contrast standard. The toggle feature should change background and border colors, but never reduce text legibility.

